"title": "8264: gentleness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8264: gentleness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An expression of compassion, seen in God's dealings with the frail and weak, and expected of believers in their dealings with others.</p>\n<h2>The gentleness of God</h2>\n<h3>In dealing with the wayward</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:1-Isa40:2\">ISA 40:1–40:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:76-Luke1:79\">LUK 1:76–1:79</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:18-Isa30:19\">ISA 30:18–30:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:8\">ISA 54:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:15\">ISA 63:15</a> <em>God's gentleness is not always evident</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:13-Hos2:15\">HOS 2:13–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a> <em>God's gentle dealings are not always appreciated.</em></p>\n<h3>In caring for the weak</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:11\">ISA 40:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs19:12\">1KI 19:12</a></p>\n<h2>The gentleness of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:29\">MAT 11:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech9:9\">ZEC 9:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:4-Matt21:5\">MAT 21:4–21:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:18-Matt12:21\">MAT 12:18–12:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1-Isa42:3\">ISA 42:1–42:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:1\">2CO 10:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:1\">PHP 2:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:2\">HEB 5:2</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of Jesus Christ's gentleness</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:40-Mark1:42\">MRK 1:40–1:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:25-Mark5:34\">MRK 5:25–5:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:13-Mark10:16\">MRK 10:13–10:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:3-John8:11\">JHN 8:3–8:11</a></p>\n<h2>Gentleness as strength esteemed by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:1\">PRO 15:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:17\">JAS 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:15\">PRO 25:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:5\">MAT 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1-1Pet3:4\">1PE 3:1–3:4</a></p>\n<h2>Gentleness as a mark of Christian character</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:22–5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:1-Eph4:2\">EPH 4:1–4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:11\">1TI 6:11</a></p>\n<h2>Believers are to reflect God's gentleness in their dealings with people</h2>\n<h3>In correcting the wayward</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:1\">GAL 6:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:24-2Tim2:25\">2TI 2:24–2:25</a></p>\n<h3>In reasoning with unbelievers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:15-1Pet3:16\">1PE 3:15–3:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>In nurturing new believers</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:7\">1TH 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>In showing consideration to all</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:1-Titus3:2\">TIT 3:1–3:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:32\">EPH 4:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:5\">PHP 4:5</a></p>",
